title: My interesting places
name: My interesting places
description:
A Map by Mgorey

Places where I have lived, places I have been to and places I would like to visit.

properties.name: Alice Springs
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyI spent a few months at Alice Springs in 1988. In fact I was there for my 21st birthday and the Australian bicentennial. It\'s an iconic inland centre.

properties.name: Bairnsdale
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyBairnsdale VictoriaA regional centre with a mixed economy about 280km east of Melbourne. I lived there in 1987.

properties.name: Ceduna
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyCedunaLived here in 1992-93. Fishing and farming town on the fringe of the agricultural zone in Eyre Peninsula. Last major town before the Nullarbor heading west.

properties.name: Eden
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyEden NSWWas a timber and fishing town when I lived there in 1994-96. Probably more tourism today. Has some great coastal scenery and an equitable climate.

properties.name: Kalgoorlie
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyWhere I live and work. Founded in the 1890s gold rush, Kalgoorlie is a major gold and nickel producing centre about 600km east of Perth and 400km inland from Esperance. The main streets are still lined with heritage buildings. The "wild west" character of the town has changed though as more families make it a residential base for working in the mines and associated industries. The town has a classic outback feel complete with red dirt and summer heat. I think it\'s more quintessentially Australian than Alice Springs, which seems to command more attention.

properties.name: Maffra
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyMaffra VictoriaA dairy farming town. I lived there from 1988 to 1991, renting a house on a farm about 5km from town.

properties.name: Melbourne
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyThe capital of Victoria, a sprawling city of more than three million people. I lived there in 1991. It\'s my favorite major city in Australia, has the most character, and it\'s home to AFL, the MCG and the Melbourne Cup.

properties.name: Porepunkah
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyPorepunkahA village of about 600 people where I lived from January 1997 to January 2006. Situated in the foothills of the Australian Alps on the Ovens and Buckland Rivers. A beautiful place with great people and some of the best scenery in Australia.

properties.name: Port Pirie
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyPort PirieLived here in 1993-94. Lead smelting town on the Spencer Gulf.

properties.name: Traralgon
properties.description: Posted by MgoreyTraralgonI grew up here. Lived in Traralgon from 1968 to 1985. Exactly 100 miles east of Melbourne, the town has a mixed economy based on power generation, softwood processing, farming, government and business.

properties.name: Warragul
properties.description: Posted by Mgoreywarragul, victoriaThe town where I was born in January 1967. Located about 80 minutes drive east of Melbourne on the Princes Highway.
